{"TopicId":102649,"ForumId":44,"TopicTitle":"So, you have a plane on a conveyor belt...","CreatedByName":"Randazzo","CreatedById":136468,"CreatedDateTime":"2015-03-25T01:29:14Z","PageNum":7,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"YNM","CreatedById":98447,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-05-14T19:37:23Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223378612\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022174940\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221526325854\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022180784\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022DAL59\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n14 minutes ago, DAL59 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYou\u003Cspan\u003E\uFEFF\u003C/span\u003E guys don\u0027t \u003Cspan\u003E\uFEFF\u003C/span\u003Enow what you\u0027re getting into\u003Cspan\u003E\uFEFF\u003C/span\u003E.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYeah, deathrap !\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler\u0022 data-ipsspoiler=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_header\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003ESpoiler\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIf we\u0027re being honest though, I suggest looking at aircraft carriers. On water and \u003Ca href=\u0022https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Airborne_aircraft_carrier\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ein air\u003C/a\u003E.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222018-05-14T19:39:30Z\u0022 title=\u002205/14/2018 07:39  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00226 yr\u0022\u003EMay 14, 2018\u003C/time\u003E by YNM\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Shpaget","CreatedById":45577,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-05-14T20:04:33Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nTreadmills have\u00A0no effect on planes. I have no idea why would anybody think otherwise. Mythbusters have checked.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsEmbeddedVideo\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022true\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 height=\u0022344\u0022 src=\u0022https://www.youtube.com/embed/YORCk1BN7QY?feature=oembed\u0022 width=\u0022459\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAnd it works in KSP as expected.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsEmbeddedVideo\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022true\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 height=\u0022270\u0022 src=\u0022https://www.youtube.com/embed/_PzVrw7MZmg?feature=oembed\u0022 width=\u0022480\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"DAL59","CreatedById":180784,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-05-14T20:10:16Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBut the plane was moving forward, so it wasn\u0027t an ideal belt.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Shpaget","CreatedById":45577,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-05-14T20:15:48Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223378645\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022174940\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221526328616\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022180784\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022DAL59\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n3 minutes ago, DAL59 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBut the plane was moving forward, so it wasn\u0027t an ideal belt.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOf course it moves forward. The belt can not make the plane move backwards if the plane applies\u00A0thrust and releases brakes.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe friction in the wheel bearings is too low to matter.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"DAL59","CreatedById":180784,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-05-14T20:33:46Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223378649\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022174940\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221526328948\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002245577\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Shpaget\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n16 minutes ago, Shpaget said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOf course it moves forward. The belt can not make the plane move backwards if the plane applies\u00A0thrust and releases brakes.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe friction in the wheel bearings is too low to matter.\u003Cspan\u003E\uFEFF\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt won\u0027t move at all, as the treadmill will move faster the faster the wheels try to move.\u00A0\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"cubinator","CreatedById":150330,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-05-14T20:39:33Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe wheels are not what is propelling the airplane. The wheels will just spin faster on a treadmill while the engines accelerate the plane to regular speed.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"DAL59","CreatedById":180784,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-05-14T20:47:54Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223378661\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022174940\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221526330373\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022150330\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022cubinator\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n7 minutes ago, cubinator said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe wheels are not what is propelling the airplane. The wheels will just spin faster on a treadmill while the engines accelerate the plane to regular speed.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBut if the engines are moving the plane, the wheels will spin as a consequence.\u00A0\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"razark","CreatedById":32993,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-05-14T20:53:20Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223378666\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022174940\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221526330874\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022180784\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022DAL59\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n4 minutes ago, DAL59 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBut if the engines are moving the plane...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThen the plane will eventually gain enough speed to take off, as there is nothing stopping the wheels from spinning freely.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"DAL59","CreatedById":180784,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-05-14T20:58:41Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223378670\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022174940\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221526331200\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002232993\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022razark\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n5 minutes ago, razark said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nas there is nothing stopping the wheels from spinning freely.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThey will spin in place due to the treadmill.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"razark","CreatedById":32993,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-05-14T21:00:34Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223378676\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022174940\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221526331521\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022180784\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022DAL59\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nJust now, DAL59 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThey will spin in place due to the treadmill.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nExcept there\u0027s nothing holding the airplane in place, so it will move forward, and the wheels will spin faster.\u00A0 Once the brakes are off and the engines throttle up, the airplane will accelerate until it reaches flying speed and leaves the ground.\u00A0 How fast the wheels are spinning doesn\u0027t matter a damn to aerodynamics.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"DAL59","CreatedById":180784,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-05-14T21:04:07Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223378679\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022174940\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221526331634\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002232993\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022razark\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n3 minutes ago, razark said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHow fast the wheels are spinning doesn\u0027t matter a damn to aerodynamics.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBut the wheels are touching the ground, which is moving backward.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"razark","CreatedById":32993,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-05-14T21:07:06Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223378681\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022174940\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221526331847\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022180784\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022DAL59\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n3 minutes ago, DAL59 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBut the wheels are touching the ground, which is moving backward.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe wheels are freely spinning.\u00A0 Airspeed matters to flying an airplane, not groundspeed.\u00A0 If an airplane with a low enough stall speed is flying into a steady headwind of sufficient speed, it can move \u0022backwards\u0022 from the ground\u0027s perspective.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nPlease explain \u003Cem\u003Ewhy\u003C/em\u003E the speed of the wheels affects the aircraft\u0027s speed.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThrust pushes the plane forward.\u00A0 To keep the plane from moving, there must be some force to counteract thrust.\u00A0 The wheels spin freely, being unconnected from anything.\u00A0 Where is the force to stop the plane coming from?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222018-05-14T21:08:31Z\u0022 title=\u002205/14/2018 09:08  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00226 yr\u0022\u003EMay 14, 2018\u003C/time\u003E by razark\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"LordFerret","CreatedById":111598,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-05-14T21:09:34Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThat video is BS.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhat generates lift on a wing gentlemen? KSP doesn\u0027t count, it\u0027s not real world physics - and you know that.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"DAL59","CreatedById":180784,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-05-14T21:11:41Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223378684\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022174940\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221526332026\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002232993\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022razark\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n4 minutes ago, razark said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhere is the force to stop the plane coming from?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe plane.\u00A0 The plane is making the treadmill move backward.\u00A0\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"razark","CreatedById":32993,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-05-14T21:13:53Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223378687\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022174940\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221526332301\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022180784\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022DAL59\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n2 minutes ago, DAL59 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe plane.\u00A0 The plane is making the treadmill move backward.\u00A0\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHow?\u00A0 The wheels of the plane are unpowered.\u00A0 The thrust comes purely from the engines.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223378685\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022174940\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221526332174\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022111598\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022LordFerret\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n4 minutes ago, LordFerret said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThat video is BS.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cbr\u003E\nWhich one?\u00A0 The KSP one, or the one that actually shows a plane taking off from (what is effectively) a treadmill?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222018-05-14T21:15:14Z\u0022 title=\u002205/14/2018 09:15  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00226 yr\u0022\u003EMay 14, 2018\u003C/time\u003E by razark\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Geonovast","CreatedById":179753,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-05-14T21:14:33Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOf course it would take off.\u00A0 Wheels mean nothing.\u00A0 It\u0027s not a car.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIf the wheels are so important, why do seaplanes work?\u00A0 Hm?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"DAL59","CreatedById":180784,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-05-14T21:17:15Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223378689\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022174940\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221526332473\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022179753\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Geonovast\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n2 minutes ago, Geonovast said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nwhy do seaplanes work?\u00A0 Hm?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSeaplanes wouldn\u0027t work if there was a current that increased linearly with how fast the plane was moving.\u00A0\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"LordFerret","CreatedById":111598,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-05-14T21:19:19Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223378688\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022174940\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221526332433\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002232993\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022razark\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n2 minutes ago, razark said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhich one?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe treadmill.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nGood gads, I can\u0027t believe you people are actually discussing this.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022http://www.explainthatstuff.com/howplaneswork.html\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttp://www.explainthatstuff.com/howplaneswork.html\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Geonovast","CreatedById":179753,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-05-14T21:20:16Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223378692\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022174940\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221526332635\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022180784\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022DAL59\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 minute ago, DAL59 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSeaplanes wouldn\u0027t work if there was a current that increased linearly with how fast the plane was moving.\u00A0\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYes they would.\u00A0 You\u0027re assuming that airplanes use friction between itself and the surface it\u0027s on to propel itself forward like cars do.\u00A0 That\u0027s just not the case.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"razark","CreatedById":32993,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-05-14T21:21:19Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223378694\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022174940\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221526332759\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022111598\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022LordFerret\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nJust now, LordFerret said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe treadmill.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSo the video of it happening is faked?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223378694\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022174940\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221526332759\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022111598\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022LordFerret\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 minute ago, LordFerret said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022http://www.explainthatstuff.com/howplaneswork.html\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttp://www.explainthatstuff.com/howplaneswork.html\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYes, airflow over the wings produces lift.\u00A0 The point is, there\u0027s nothing holding the airplane from moving, it will accelerate, air will flow over the lifting surface, and the plane will take off.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Geonovast","CreatedById":179753,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-05-14T21:23:48Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nTie the plane\u0027s prop to a tree.\u00A0 Run the treadmill.\u00A0 If you\u0027re right, the treadmill would be unable to run because the plane could not move backwards.\u00A0 But the treadmill will work fine, because the wheels will just keep spinning, just keep spinning, spinning, just keep spinning, spinning, spinning...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"NSEP","CreatedById":165635,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-05-14T21:24:42Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNo, because it needs air to push on the wings in order to generate lift. The plane is essentially standing still while on a treadmill. Wheels have nothing to do with how a plane takes off other than decrease friction on the runway.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"LordFerret","CreatedById":111598,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-05-14T21:24:49Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/32993-razark/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u002232993\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/32993-razark/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@razark\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe MythBusters video is misleading. If truly a conveyor varied its speed to a point to hold a real airplane \u003Cu\u003Esteady in one place\u003C/u\u003E, which is the concept/question asked in the \u003Cabbr title=\u00221. Original Post(er). The first post in a thread, or the person who posted it. 2. Overpowered. A part or mechanic that upsets game balance by being too powerful.\u0022\u003EOP\u003C/abbr\u003E, it \u003Cu\u003Ewould not\u003C/u\u003E fly. For a plane to fly, the engines must pull it forward... the forward motion causes air to pass over the wings, which generates lift.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Geonovast","CreatedById":179753,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-05-14T21:26:28Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223378704\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022174940\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221526333089\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022111598\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022LordFerret\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n3 minutes ago, LordFerret said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/32993-razark/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u002232993\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/32993-razark/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@razark\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe MythBusters video is misleading. If truly a conveyor varied its speed to a point to hold a real airplane \u003Cu\u003Esteady in one place\u003C/u\u003E, which is the concept/question asked in the \u003Cabbr title=\u00221. Original Post(er). The first post in a thread, or the person who posted it. 2. Overpowered. A part or mechanic that upsets game balance by being too powerful.\u0022\u003EOP\u003C/abbr\u003E, it \u003Cu\u003Ewould not\u003C/u\u003E fly. For a plane to fly, the engines must pull it forward... the forward motion causes air to pass over the wings, which generates lift.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBut the treadmill \u003Cem\u003Ewill not pull it backwards if it is pulling itself forward. \u003C/em\u003EIt might have to try an insignificant amount more to overcome the friction from the wheels, but it will take off just fine.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nFine, how about this.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nPut a car on the treadmill.\u00A0 Magically start the car going at a certain speed, and the treadmill at the same speed in the opposite direction.\u00A0 Car stays put, right?\u00A0 Because the car has to push against the treadmill to move forward.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNow put the car in neutral, and attach a chain from the front on the car to the back of another car in front of it, which is not on the treadmill.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nStart the treadmill, and Accelerate the second car up front.\u00A0 By your logic, the car on the treadmill will stay put instead of being pulled off.\u00A0 Right?\u00A0 Nerp.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe planes wheels are always in neutral, like the car.\u00A0 The prop is the second car pulling it off the treadmill.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222018-05-14T21:29:07Z\u0022 title=\u002205/14/2018 09:29  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00226 yr\u0022\u003EMay 14, 2018\u003C/time\u003E by Geonovast\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"LordFerret","CreatedById":111598,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-05-14T21:28:38Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAgain, you\u0027re missing it. If the plane is held stationary, wheels spinning, engine roaring, without air passing over the wings there will be no lift - no flight.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nRead the link damnit.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}